dream_edit.guide.import:
A guide on how to import into another world:
 A chest appeared under you, look at it and press F3 + I to copy it, and in another world execute a command in the command block (do not forget to change the coordinates) and stand on that chest after completing these Dream Edit operations will automatically save it in memory.

dream_edit.nbt.hints.rotationx: Changes the entity rotation on X axis
dream_edit.nbt.hints.rotationy: Changes the entity rotation on Y axis
dream_edit.nbt.hints.posx: The X axis entity on world.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.posy: The Y axis entity on world.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.posz: The Z axis entity on world.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.nogravity: Makes mobs unaffected by gravity. Mobs will not fall.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.slient:
Makes mobs silent.
(Does not work for certain sounds)
dream_edit.nbt.hints.fire: Determines how many ticks a mob is on fire.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.size: Changes the size of a slime, magma cube or phantom
dream_edit.nbt.hints.canpickiploot: Determines can entity pick up loot.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.persistencerequired: Determines a entity will despawn naturally or not
dream_edit.nbt.hints.lefthanded: 1 or 0 (true/false) - true if the mob renders the main hand as being left.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.leashed: Determines a entity is leashed or not.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.health: The number of health points the entity has
dream_edit.nbt.hints.monsionx: Determines the velocity of most entities on X axis.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.monsiony: Determines the velocity of most entities on Y axis.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.monsionz: Determines the velocity of most entities on Z axis.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.customnamevisible:
1 or 0 (true/false) - if true, and this entity has a
custom name, the name always appears above the entity
dream_edit.nbt.hints.falldistance: Distance the entity has fallen. Larger values cause more damage when the entity lands.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.slepingx: The X coordinate of where the entity is sleeping, absent if not sleeping.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.slepingy: The Y coordinate of where the entity is sleeping, absent if not sleeping.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.slepingz: The Z coordinate of where the entity is sleeping, absent if not sleeping.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.portalcooldown:
The number of ticks before which the entity may be teleported back through a nether portal.
Initially starts at 300 ticks (15 seconds) after teleportation and counts down to 0.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.hurttime: Number of ticks the mob turns red for after being hit. 0 when not recently hit.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.hurtbytimestamp:
The last time the mob was damaged, measured in the number of ticks since the mob's creation.
Updates to a new value whenever the mob is damaged,
then updates again 101 ticks later for reasons unknown.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.deathtime: Number of ticks the mob has been dead for. Controls death animations. 0 when alive.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.air: The number of game ticks the entity has air left for
dream_edit.nbt.hints.noai: Makes mobs have no AI. Mobs will not move on their own.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.invulnerable:
Makes mobs invulnerable to everything except
the Void and players in Creative Mode.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.leashx: Indicates the X axis of the fence that the entity is leashed to.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.leashy: Indicates the Y axis of the fence that the entity is leashed to.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.leashz: Indicates the Z axis of the fence that the entity is leashed to.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.fallflying: Determines a entity can use elytra or not
dream_edit.nbt.hints.glowing: Determines a entity is glowing or not
dream_edit.nbt.hints.isbaby: 1 or 0 (true/false) - true if this zombie is a baby. May be absent.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.canbreakdoors: 1 or 0 (true/false) - true if the zombie can break doors (default value is 0).
dream_edit.nbt.hints.drownedconversionti:
The number of ticks until this zombie converts to a
drowned, or husk to zombie.
(default value is -1, when no conversion is under way).
dream_edit.nbt.hints.inwatertime:
The number of ticks this zombie or husk has been under water,
used to start the drowning conversion.
(default value is -1, when no conversion is under way).
dream_edit.nbt.hints.inlove:
Number of ticks until the mob 
loses its breeding hearts and stops searching for a mate.
0 when not searching for a mate.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.age:
Represents the age of the mob in ticks; when negative,
the mob is a baby. When 0 or above, the mob is an adult.
When above 0, represents the number of ticks before this mob can breed again.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.forcedage:
A value of age assigned to this mob when it grows up.
Incremented when a baby mob is fed.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.lovecause: The entity uuid that caused this animal to breed, stored as four ints.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.owner: The player who owns the entityy
dream_edit.nbt.hints.hasegg: Determines if the turtle has an egg to lay
dream_edit.nbt.hints.travelposx:
Determines the distance a turtle can lay
eggs from its home coordinates, on the X axis.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.travelposy:
Determines the distance a turtle can lay
eggs from its home coordinates, on the Y axis.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.travelposz:
Determines the distance a turtle can lay
eggs from its home coordinates, on the Z axis.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.homeposx: Determines the X coordinate of a turtle's home beach.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.homeposy: Determines the Y coordinate of a turtle's home beach.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.homeposz: Determines the Z coordinate of a turtle's home beach.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.powered: Determines whether a Creeper is charged or not
dream_edit.nbt.hints.ignited: Determines a Creeper is ignited or not
dream_edit.nbt.hints.explosionradius: Set the radius of the explosion
dream_edit.nbt.hints.fuse: The number of game ticks until the creeper explodes
dream_edit.nbt.hints.showarms: Determines whether you can see the armor stand's arms or not.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.nobaseplate: Determines whether the armor stand has a base plate or not.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.small: Determines whether the armor stand is small or not.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.invisible: Determines whether the armor stand is invisible or not.
dream_edit.nbt.hints.pose: Changes the pose of the armor stand's body parts.
